        "text": "What is a Quadratic Equation?",
        "level": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "data": {
        "text": "A quadratic equation is an equation of the form $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$ where $a \\neq 0$."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "math",
      "data": {
        "latex": "ax^2 + bx + c = 0, \\quad a \\neq 0",
        "display": true
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "data": {
        "text": "Key Components",
        "level": 3
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "style": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "$a$ is the quadratic coefficient",
          "$b$ is the linear coefficient",
          "$c$ is the constant term"
        ]
      }
    },
